Kirinyaga Central MP aspirant Josiah Murigu has denied claims Jubilee Party officials are planning to give him a direct ticket.Incumbent Joseph Gitari will run for governor. Speaking at Kerugoya Goodhope Children&rsquo;s Home in Kerugoya on Sunday, Murigo told his competitors to be mature and stop spreading propaganda. He donated food and clothing. Murigo told his opponents to prepare for a bruising battle in the primaries.He said he is keen on winning the JP ticket because the party is the most popular in Central.Murigu resigned from his job as a journalist to run. He is considered a top contendor in the race, which has attracted 18 candidates. Murigu called for peaceful campaigns.